---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const title = 'Chartly documentation';
---
<BaseLayout title={title}>
  <section>
    <p>Welcome to the Chartly docs site. This Astro-powered site is the home for guides, examples, and API reference for the Chartly charting library.</p>
  </section>
  <section>
    <h2>Getting started</h2>
    <p>Run the docs dev server with:</p>
    <pre><code>npm run dev</code></pre>
    <p>Then open <code>http://localhost:5173</code> in your browser.</p>
  </section>
  <section>
    <h2>Next steps</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Build the library package: <code>cd ../chartly && npm run build</code></li>
      <li>Add chart examples using React components from <code>chartly</code></li>
      <li>Create MDX pages for guides and API docs</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
